# What are Control Statements?

Control statements are statements that control the flow of execution of a program based on conditions or repetition.

They help the program make decisions.

---

# Types of Control Statements

```
Control Statements

│

├── Decision Making
│     ├── if
│     ├── if-else
│     ├── else-if
│     └── switch
│
├── Looping
│     ├── for
│     ├── while
│     └── do-while
│
└── Jump Statements
      ├── break
      ├── continue
      └── return
```

---

# Why Do We Need Control Statements?

Without control statements, every statement executes one after another.

Control statements allow programs to make decisions.

Example

```java
if(age >= 18){
    System.out.println("Eligible to Vote");
}
```

---

# if Statement

## Syntax

```java
if(condition){
    // statements
}
```

If the condition is `true`, the block executes.

If the condition is `false`, the block is skipped.

---

## Example

```java
int age = 20;

if(age >= 18){
    System.out.println("Eligible");
}
```

Output

```
Eligible
```

---

# if-else Statement

Used when one block should execute if the condition is true and another block should execute if the condition is false.

## Syntax

```java
if(condition){

}
else{

}
```

---

## Example

```java
int marks = 35;

if(marks >= 40){
    System.out.println("Pass");
}
else{
    System.out.println("Fail");
}
```

Output

```
Fail
```

---

# else-if Ladder

Used when multiple conditions need to be checked.

## Syntax

```java
if(condition1){

}
else if(condition2){

}
else if(condition3){

}
else{

}
```

Java checks conditions from top to bottom.

As soon as one condition becomes true, the corresponding block executes and the remaining conditions are skipped.

---

## Example

```java
int marks = 82;

if(marks >= 90){
    System.out.println("Grade A");
}
else if(marks >= 75){
    System.out.println("Grade B");
}
else if(marks >= 50){
    System.out.println("Grade C");
}
else{
    System.out.println("Fail");
}
```

Output

```
Grade B
```

---

# Nested if

A nested if is an if statement inside another if statement.

Example

```java
int age = 25;
boolean hasLicense = true;

if(age >= 18){

    if(hasLicense){
        System.out.println("Can Drive");
    }

}
```

Output

```
Can Drive
```

